\section*{Aims and Objectives}
This course aims to provide you with a broad overview of some of the key areas in the area of financial services.  There are two components to the module:  knowledge and understanding of key financial institutions and financial markets; applying knowledge of finance to create an investment portfolio.  The main topics that will be covered in this module are:  
\begin{itemize}
\item The role and functioning of the financial system and the way that various elements are interrelated. The influence of the financial system on corporate behaviour. 
\item The varied characteristics of the financial system in different countries and the way that this may affect the process of financial intermediation.
\item	Features of money, bond and equity finance and methods of evaluating the performance of bonds and equities. 
\item The international aspect of the capital markets. The determination of foreign exchange and the arguments for and against relaxation of capital account controls. 
\item The interaction between regulation and innovation.  The debate about the level of regulation that is socially optimal.  The characteristics of financial innovation.  
\item The ideas of Modern Portfolio Theory and Capital Asset Pricing and how these can be applied in practice.  
\item The operation of the market.  The way that structure affects liquidity and price discovery.  Market-making against electronic markets. \item The scientific method and the role of evidence in the testing of theories.  
\end{itemize}

