\section*{Teaching Methods}

Each week a key concept will be covered in the lecture and in the seminar class of the following week.  We use the seminar class to discuss article and exercises that have been give for preparatory work.  It is essential that you complete this preparatory work if you are going to get a good grade as it will ensure that you fully understand the foundation topics before we move on to more challenging subjects. We will use the Rotman Interactive Trading software to give you a feel for how trading in financial markets is carried out. 

\section*{Assessment}
There are two assessments.  At the end of the year there is an unseen 3-hour exam. The exam will be based on what we cover in the lectures and seminars.  There is also a 1,250 word report on your investment portfolio.  The portfolio can be constructed using whatever means that you believe will be successful.  We aim to have the portfolio constructed by early January so that we can monitor its performance through the first half of the year.  You report will combine some discussion of the thinking behind your construction0on of the portfolio as well as an overview of the investment performance. 

